# Undo / history

- **Push:** Semantic graph edits (nodes, connections, parameters, automation on the graph, etc.) go through **`graphStore`**; the store calls `graphChangedListener` → `undoRedoManager.pushState(graph)` for those paths. **Pan/zoom/selection** (`updateViewState`) notifies the listener with `recordUndo: false` so undo history stays semantic-only; applying undo/redo merges **live** view state onto the snapshot before `setGraph`.
- **Preset / full replace:** `undoRedoManager.clear()` then `graphStore.setGraph(...)` so history starts from the loaded graph.

**Don’t:** Mutate graph outside store (or bypass listener); push duplicate state on preset load.

**Refs:** `graphStore.svelte.ts` (`setGraphChangedListener`), `.cursor/rules/data-model/graph-updates.mdc`, `docs/user-goals/11-undo-redo-and-keyboard.md`, `docs/user-goals/08-presets-and-data.md`.
